---
title: WOCS Phase 1 - Core Class Model (Low Level Design)
---
classDiagram
    class User {
        +UUID userId
        +String role
        +String name
        +login()
        +hasPermission()
    }
    
    class Warehouse {
        +String warehouseId
        +String type
        +boolean mandatoryLocation
        +boolean mandatorySerial
    }
    
    class InventoryItem {
        +UUID itemId
        +UUID clientId
        +String sku
        +int quantity
        +String batchLot
        +Date expiryDate
        +String storageType
        +String location
        +adjustQuantity(newVal, reason, user)
        +transfer(warehouseId)
    }
    
    class Order {
        +UUID orderId
        +UUID clientId
        +String deliveryAddress
        +String shippingMethod
        +String status
        +DateTime slaStartTime
        +DateTime dispatchTime
        +updateState(newState, user)
    }
    
    class OrderLineItem {
        +UUID lineItemId
        +String sku
        +int quantity
    }
    
    class SLAConfig {
        +UUID clientId
        +int slaDurationHours
        +String slaStartStatus
        +checkBreach(currentTime, dispatchTime)
    }
    
    class BillingRate {
        +UUID clientId
        +String warehouseId
        +String activityType
        +float rate
        +Date effectiveDate
        +calculateCharge(quantity)
    }
    
    class AuditLog {
        +UUID logId
        +UUID userId
        +DateTime timestamp
        +String action
        +String previousState
        +String newState
    }
    
    Order "1" *-- "*" OrderLineItem : contains
    Order --> SLAConfig : governed by
    InventoryItem --> AuditLog : logs to
    Order --> AuditLog : logs to
    Warehouse "1" --> "*" InventoryItem : stores

---
title: Sequence Diagram - Order Fulfillment, SLA Monitoring, and Billing (Low Level Design)
---
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Client
    participant API as WOCS API
    participant OM as Order Service
    participant SLA as SLA Engine
    participant BM as Billing Service
    participant DB as WOCS Database
    actor Operator as Warehouse Handheld

    Client->>API: Submit Order (API/File/Manual)
    API->>OM: Create Order (Status: Received)
    OM->>DB: Save Order & Create Creation Audit Log
    OM->>SLA: Start SLA Timer (Configured for Client)
    API-->>Client: Acknowledgment of Order Receipt

    %% Order Fulfillment Workflow & Progress
    Operator->>OM: Scan Barcode (Pick Items Workflow)
    OM->>DB: Update Order State (Picked) & Generate Audit Log
    OM->>BM: Trigger Picking Charge Calc (Rate * Qty)
    
    Operator->>OM: Pack Items Workflow
    OM->>DB: Update Order State (Packed) & Generate Audit Log

    %% Async SLA Monitoring Check
    activate SLA
    SLA->>SLA: Async Check: (CurrentTime > SLA_Start + Duration - 2h)
    SLA-->>Operator: 2-hour SLA Warning Alert / Notification
    deactivate SLA

    Operator->>OM: Dispatch Order to Shipper
    OM->>DB: Update State (Dispatched) & Generate Audit Log
    
    OM->>SLA: Stop SLA Timer & Evaluate Final SLA Goal
    alt Dispatch Time <= SLA Duration Configured
        SLA->>DB: Flag Order as SLA Compliant
    else Dispatch Time > SLA Duration Configured
        SLA->>DB: Flag Order as SLA Breached (For Reporting)
    end

    OM->>BM: Trigger Handling Charge Calculation (Fixed Rate)

---
title: Sequence Diagram - Inventory Adjustment (Low Level Design)
---
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor WM as Warehouse Manager
    participant API as WOCS API
    participant IM as Inventory Service
    participant DB as WOCS Database

    WM->>API: Submit Inventory Adjustment (SKU, Qty, Reason)
    API->>IM: Process Adjustment Request
    IM->>DB: Fetch Current Quantity & Location Config
    DB-->>IM: Current Qty = 100, Mandatory Location = True

    IM->>IM: Calculate Difference
    IM->>DB: Update Qty in Location (New Qty)
    
    IM->>DB: Insert Audit Log (Prev: 100, New: Adjusted, Reason, UserID, Timestamp)
    DB-->>IM: Commit Success

    IM-->>API: Return Validation Success
    API-->>WM: Adjust Successful Alert
